- "lineage" represents the hierarchical relationship from top-level managers to their subordinates;
- "performance ratings" are the individual ratings of employees' performance;
- "average performance of its offspring" refers to the average performance ratings of an employee's direct and indirect subordinates;
- "overall company sentiment" is the sentiment score derived from the ratings, indicating the general mood or perception within the company.

