- "Performance rating" is a score from 1 to 5, with 5 being the best;
- "Years at company" is the duration of employment, with "5 years" being the threshold for long-term employees.

- "A strong workforce" refers to departments with more than 5 employees;
- "A high level of satisfaction" means an average overall company rating greater than 3.5;
- "More than a handful" is a metaphor for more than 5 employees;
- "Above average" indicates a rating greater than 3.5 on a scale of 1 to 5.

